          xmlns:ml="http://xmlcalabash.com/ns/extensions/marklogic"
          xmlns:cxu="http://xmlcalabash.com/ns/extensions/xmlunit"
          xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
          xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
          xmlns:pos="http://exproc.org/proposed/steps/os"
          xml:id="cx-java-properties">
   <refnamediv>
      <refname>cx:java-properties</refname>
      <refpurpose>Reads a Java properties file</refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
   <refsynopsisdiv>
      <xi:include href="../declarations.xml" xpointer="xpath(/*/*[@type='cx:java-properties'])"/>
   </refsynopsisdiv>
   <refsection>
      <title>Description</title>

<para>The <tag>cx:java-properties</tag> step reads a Java properties file and
returns it as a <tag>c:param-set</tag>.
</para>

<para>If <option>href</option> is specified, it must be the URI of a properties file. It will
be made absolute relative to the base URI of the element on which it occurs. If
<option>href</option> is not specified, the Java system properties are returned.</para>

   </refsection>
</refentry>